      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so the school is basically following what they see as research-backed best practices to protect kids. it's hard to argue with that if it helps stop bullying. but then you have these parents who are basically calling it a political mandate. do you think their concerns are actually valid, or is that just an excuse to avoid the topic of inclusion?",
